Introduction ‚Äã

Excellent Data Filler is a powerful browser extension that automates data entry tasks across web forms. Whether you need to fill forms repeatedly, generate Excel reports, or automate complex workflows, this extension provides the tools you need to save time and reduce manual errors.

Key Features ‚Äã

üîÑ Auto Fill Form Fields Automatically populate form fields with predefined or dynamic data
üìä Auto Generate Excel Create and export data to Excel files with custom formatting
üñ±Ô∏è Auto Click Buttons Automate button clicks and form submissions
‚ö° Run Custom JavaScript Execute custom scripts for advanced automation
üíæ Store Entry Response Save and manage form submission responses
üåê Universal Compatibility Works with Google Forms, Microsoft Forms, and virtually any web form
üìã Data Templates Create reusable data templates for consistent form filling
üîß Advanced Field Types Support for text, dropdowns, checkboxes, file uploads, and more

Quick Start ‚Äã

Follow these simple steps to get started with Excellent Data Filler:

Step 1: Install the Extension ‚Äã

  1. Download the extension for your preferred browser
  2. Follow the browser-specific installation instructions
  3. The extension icon will appear in your browser toolbar

Step 2: Set Up Your First Site ‚Äã

  1. Navigate to the web page with the form you want to automate
  2. Right-click on the extension icon in your toolbar
  3. Select "Insert Site" from the context menu
  4. Alternatively, right-click directly on the form and choose the extension option

Step 3: Configure Form Fields ‚Äã

  1. The extension will automatically detect form fields on the page
  2. Configure each field with your desired data source (static text, Excel data, variables, etc.)
  3. Set up any special actions like file uploads or custom JavaScript

Step 4: Run Your Automation ‚Äã

Refresh the page and the extension will automatically fill the form fields. If any action not running in the form then you can check extension Log for more details.

üí° Pro Tip: Start with simple forms to get familiar with the extension, then gradually work up to more complex automation scenarios.
